Sentencas: A basic requirement for solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs) is the sintering of electrolyte into a dense impermeable membrane to prevent the mixing of fuel and oxygen for a sufficiently high open-circuit voltage (OCV).
Titulo: Carbonate-superstructured solid fuel cells with hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: However, herein, we demonstrate a different type of fuel cell, a carbonate-superstructured solid fuel cell (CSSFC), in which in situ generation of superstructured carbonate in the porous samarium-doped ceria layer creates a unique electrolyte with ultrahigh ionic conductivity of 0.17 S center dot cm(-1) at 550 degrees C.
Titulo: Carbonate-superstructured solid fuel cells with hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: The CSSFC achieves unprecedented high OCVs (1.051 V at 500 degrees C and 1.041 V at 550 degrees C) with methane fuel.
Titulo: Carbonate-superstructured solid fuel cells with hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: Furthermore, the CSSFC exhibits a high peak power density of 215 mW center dot cm(-2) with dry methane fuel at 550 degrees C, which is higher than all reported values of electrolyte-supported SOFCs.
Titulo: Carbonate-superstructured solid fuel cells with hydrocarbon fuels

Sentencas: This provides a different approach for the development of efficient solid fuel cells.
Titulo: Carbonate-superstructured solid fuel cells with hydrocarbon fuels
